00:07:10.760 --> 00:07:34.340
Yeah, for sure. So a lot of the benefit of using Pydantic is we promise some great performance. And a lot of those performance gains came during our jump from V1 to V2. So V1 was written solely in Python. We had some compiled options, but really it was mostly Pythonic data validation.

00:07:34.600 --> 00:07:38.860
or I say Pythonic, it's always Pythonic, but data validation done solely in Python.

00:07:40.400 --> 00:07:46.800
