you're doing it wrong, you know, that would be great. Yeah, definitely. Yeah, some of those

00:23:40.040 --> 00:23:45.520
errors can be pretty cryptic with the syntax stuff. And they can. All right. So be specific,

00:23:45.920 --> 00:23:52.060
list tuple, not sequence, if you know it's a list or tuple or whatever. Yeah. And then kind of my

00:23:52.220 --> 00:23:58.680
last minor tip, which great that you brought up import statements, and kind of adding general time

00:23:58.860 --> 00:24:03.980
to a program is, I don't have a slide for this one. But if we go back to the type adapter slide,

00:24:04.540 --> 00:24:11.880
we talked about the fact that initializing this type adapter builds a core schema and attaches it to that class.

00:24:12.780 --> 00:24:16.720
And that's kind of done at build time, at import time.

00:24:17.140 --> 00:24:18.920
So that's already done.

00:24:20.300 --> 00:24:26.360
And if you really don't want to have that import or build time take a long time,

00:24:26.720 --> 00:24:29.620
