00:24:30.300 --> 00:24:34.560
And so what that does is defers the core schema build until the first validation call.

00:24:34.740 --> 00:24:37.940
You can also set that on model config and things like that.

00:24:38.200 --> 00:24:42.220
But basically the idea here is like striving to be lazier, right?

00:24:42.460 --> 00:24:47.440
Like if we don't need to build this core schema right at import time, because we want our

00:24:47.700 --> 00:24:49.200
program to start up quickly, that's great.

00:24:49.300 --> 00:24:53.660
We might have a little bit of a delay on the first validation, but maybe startup time is

00:24:53.720 --> 00:24:54.160
more important.

00:24:54.440 --> 00:24:58.880
So that's a little bit more of a preferential validation, sorry, preferential performance

00:24:59.120 --> 00:24:59.240
tip.

00:24:59.840 --> 00:25:01.780
but available for folks who need it.

