Let's close it out for us

00:55:46.700 --> 00:55:48.818
with maybe final call to action

00:55:48.840 --> 00:55:51.620
for people who are already using Pydantic

00:55:52.500 --> 00:55:54.080
and they want it to go faster

00:55:54.560 --> 00:55:55.980
or maybe they could adopt some of these tips.

00:55:56.040 --> 00:55:56.500
What do you tell them?

00:55:57.780 --> 00:56:00.360
Yeah, I would say, you know,

00:56:01.440 --> 00:56:02.700
inform yourself just a little bit

00:56:02.880 --> 00:56:05.560
about kind of the Pydantic architecture

00:56:05.860 --> 00:56:08.000
just in terms of like, what is core schema

00:56:08.360 --> 00:56:10.920
and why are we using Rust for validation and serialization?

00:56:11.780 --> 00:56:13.560
And then that can kind of take you to the next steps

00:56:14.040 --> 00:56:16.500
of when do I want to build my core schemas

00:56:16.660 --> 00:56:18.320
based on kind of the nature of my application?

00:56:18.800 --> 00:56:22.260
Is it okay if imports take a little bit longer or do I want to delay that?

00:56:23.220 --> 00:56:24.840
And then take a look at discriminated unions.

00:56:26.300 --> 00:56:29.640
And then maybe if you're really interested in improving performance across your application

00:56:30.000 --> 00:56:31.860
that supports Pydantic and other things,

00:56:33.240 --> 00:56:36.080
trying out Logfire and just seeing what sort of benefits you can get there.

00:56:36.840 --> 00:56:36.900
Yeah.

00:56:37.130 --> 00:56:41.180
See where you're spending your time is one of the very, you know,

00:56:42.080 --> 00:56:44.140
not just focused on Pydantic, but in general,

00:56:45.020 --> 00:56:50.820
our intuition is often pretty bad for where is your code slow and where is it not slow?

00:56:50.860 --> 00:56:52.300
You're like, that looks really complicated.

00:56:52.460 --> 00:56:53.040
That must be slow.

00:56:53.120 --> 00:56:53.480
Like, nope.

00:56:53.900 --> 00:56:57.820
It's that one call to like some sub module that you didn't realize was terrible.

00:56:59.120 --> 00:56:59.200
Yeah.

00:56:59.640 --> 00:56:59.780
Yeah.

